1. OVERVIEW

This command line application "mbtSearch" contains functions for loading
sets of binary vectors (fingerprints) into a search tree and perform fast
similarity matching. As measure of similarity can be applied as Tanimoto-
or Hamming-Coefficient. The search tree's data structure and algorithms
are based on a combination of 1DGrid, Symdex, Multibit Tree, Union Tree
and XOR-folding as discribed in the articles referenced below.

